  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Sequence Proof and Enforcement</title>\n<style>\n  :root {\n    --bg: #faf7f1;\n    --fg: #1a1a1a;\n    --muted: #6b6b6b;\n    --line: #e5e0d6;\n    --blue: #4a7ba7;\n    --amber: #f59e0b;\n    --red: #dc2626;\n  }\n  * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n  body {\n    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif;\n    margin: 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    color: var(--fg);\n    background: var(--bg);\n    line-height: 1.5;\n  }\n  h2 {\n    font-size: 1.05rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    margin: 0 0 4px;\n  }\n  p.subhead {\n    margin: 0 0 8px;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  p.concept {\n    margin: 0 0 20px;\n    color: var(--fg);\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n    font-style: italic;\n  }\n  .control {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 14px;\n    margin-bottom: 24px;\n  }\n  .control label {\n    font-weight: 500;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n  }\n  .control input[type=range] {\n    flex: 1;\n    accent-color: var(--blue);\n    min-width: 120px;\n  }\n  .control output {\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    min-width: 4ch;\n    text-align: right;\n  }\n  .log {\n    margin: 24px 0;\n    padding: 16px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n  }\n  .log-label {\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.06em;\n    margin-bottom: 12px;\n  }\n  .events {\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n    gap: 6px;\n  }\n  .event {\n    display: grid;\n    grid-template-columns: auto 4ch 1fr;\n    gap: 10px;\n    align-items: center;\n    padding: 6px 10px;\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    font-size: 0.85rem;\n    background: #f9f9f9;\n  }\n  .event-time {\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    color: var(--muted);\n  }\n  .event-actor {\n    font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  .event-action {\n    color: var(--muted);\n  }\n  .claims {\n    display: grid;\n    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;\n    gap: 14px;\n    margin: 20px 0;\n  }\n  .claim {\n    padding: 12px 14px;\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    font-size: 0.85rem;\n  }\n  .claim-label {\n    font-weight: 600;\n    margin-bottom: 4px;\n  }\n  .claim-text {\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.8rem;\n  }\n  .claim.ok {\n    background: #e8f5e9;\n  }\n  .claim.dispute {\n    background: #fff3e0;\n  }\n  .reading {\n    margin: 20px 0 6px;\n    padding: 12px 16px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .reading strong {\n    font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  p.caption {\n    margin: 14px 0 0;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.875rem;\n  }\n  @media (max-width: 560px) {\n    .claims {\n      grid-template-columns: 1fr;\n    }\n    .event {\n      grid-template-columns: auto 3ch 1fr;\n      gap: 8px;\n    }\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2>Adjust timestamp precision</h2>\n<p class=\"subhead\">Both parties signed an agreement to stop attacks. The monitor records four events.</p>\n<p class=\"concept\">When a monitoring system records events but cannot prove their order, each party can claim response to the other's breach, making enforcement impossible.</p>\n\n<div class=\"control\">\n  <label for=\"precision\">Precision:</label>\n  <input id=\"precision\" type=\"range\" min=\"1\" max=\"4\" value=\"4\" step=\"1\" aria-describedby=\"precision-out\">\n  <output id=\"precision-out\" for=\"precision\">±1 min</output>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"log\">\n  <div class=\"log-label\">Monitor event log</div>\n  <div class=\"events\" id=\"events\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"claims\">\n  <div class=\"claim\" id=\"claim-x\">\n    <div class=\"claim-label\">Party X</div>\n    <div class=\"claim-text\" id=\"text-x\"></div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"claim\" id=\"claim-y\">\n    <div class=\"claim-label\">Party Y</div>\n    <div class=\"claim-text\" id=\"text-y\"></div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"reading\">\n  <strong id=\"enforcement\"></strong>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"caption\" id=\"caption\"></p>\n\n<script>\n  (function () {\n    var slider = document.getElementById('precision');\n    var precOut = document.getElementById('precision-out');\n    var eventsEl = document.getElementById('events');\n    var claimX = document.getElementById('claim-x');\n    var claimY = document.getElementById('claim-y');\n    var textX = document.getElementById('text-x');\n    var textY = document.getElementById('text-y');\n    var enforcement = document.getElementById('enforcement');\n    var caption = document.getElementById('caption');\n\n    var trueOrder = [\n      { actor: 'X', action: 'Strike near boundary', trueTime: 847 },\n      { actor: 'Y', action: 'Counterstrike', trueTime: 851 },\n      { actor: 'X', action: 'Second strike', trueTime: 902 },\n      { actor: 'Y', action: 'Defensive response', trueTime: 908 }\n    ];\n\n    var labels = ['±30 min', '±10 min', '±5 min', '±1 min'];\n\n    function formatTime(minutes) {\n      var h = Math.floor(minutes / 60);\n      var m = minutes % 60;\n      return ('0' + h).slice(-2) + ':' + ('0' + m).slice(-2);\n    }\n\n    function render() {\n      var prec = +slider.value;\n      precOut.textContent = labels[prec - 1];\n\n      var windows = [30, 10, 5, 1];\n      var window = windows[prec - 1];\n\n      eventsEl.innerHTML = '';\n      for (var i = 0; i < trueOrder.length; i++) {\n        var ev = trueOrder[i];\n        var lower = ev.trueTime - window;\n        var upper = ev.trueTime + window;\n        var timeStr = formatTime(lower) + '–' + formatTime(upper);\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'event';\n        div.innerHTML =\n          '<span class=\"event-time\">' + timeStr + '</span>' +\n          '<span class=\"event-actor\">' + ev.actor + '</span>' +\n          '<span class=\"event-action\">' + ev.action + '</span>';\n        eventsEl.appendChild(div);\n      }\n\n      if (prec === 4) {\n        claimX.className = 'claim ok';\n        claimY.className = 'claim ok';\n        textX.textContent = 'X acted at 14:07, then 15:02.';\n        textY.textContent = 'Y responded at 14:11, then 15:08.';\n        enforcement.textContent = 'Timestamps prove X fired first. Enforcement proceeds against X.';\n        caption.textContent = 'Narrow time windows separate breach from response. The monitor can prove who violated the agreement, making punishment possible.';\n      } else if (prec === 3) {\n        claimX.className = 'claim dispute';\n        claimY.className = 'claim dispute';\n        textX.textContent = 'Y fired somewhere in the 14:06–14:16 window — we responded.';\n        textY.textContent = 'X fired somewhere in the 14:02–14:12 window — we responded.';\n        enforcement.textContent = 'Time windows overlap. Both parties claim self-defense. Monitor cannot determine first strike.';\n        caption.textContent = 'Five-minute windows create ambiguity. The monitor sees all four events but cannot prove order. Each side's claim is equally plausible.';\n      } else if (prec === 2) {\n        claimX.className = 'claim dispute';\n        claimY.className = 'claim dispute';\n        textX.textContent = 'Y clearly acted first — look at the log.';\n        textY.textContent = 'X clearly acted first — look at the log.';\n        enforcement.textContent = 'Wide time windows make sequence indeterminate. Both interpretations fit the data.';\n        caption.textContent = 'Ten-minute windows erase sequence. Both parties point to the same log and reach opposite conclusions. Enforcement collapses.';\n      } else {\n        claimX.className = 'claim dispute';\n        claimY.className = 'claim dispute';\n        textX.textContent = 'All our actions were responses to Y.';\n        textY.textContent = 'All our actions were responses to X.';\n        enforcement.textContent = 'Timestamps so coarse they prove nothing. Agreement unenforceable.';\n        caption.textContent = 'Thirty-minute windows destroy accountability. The monitor records events but cannot separate breach from retaliation. Without proof of sequence, punishment becomes arbitrary.';\n      }\n    }\n\n    slider.addEventListener('input', render);\n    render();\n  })();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
